results.name: Triangle T(n,k) (n >= 3, k = 1..n-2) read by rows, giving number of nonisomorphic oriented matroids with n points in n-k dimensions.
reference: Lukas Finschi, A Graph Theoretical Approach for Reconstruction and Generation of Oriented Matroids, A dissertation submitted to the Swiss Federal Institute of Technology, Zurich for the degree of Doctor of Mathematics, 2001.

Fukuda, Komei; Miyata, Hiroyuki; Moriyama, Sonoko. Complete Enumeration of Small Realizable Oriented Matroids. Discrete Comput. Geom. 49 (2013), no. 2, 359--381. MR3017917. - From _N. J. A. Sloane_, Feb 16 2013
link: L. Finschi and K. Fukuda, Complete combinatorial generation of small point set configurations and hyperplane arrangements, pp. 97-100 in Abstracts 13th Canadian Conference on Computational Geometry (CCCG '01), Waterloo, Aug. 13-15, 2001.
xref: Diagonals give A063800-A063803, A246988, A246989. Row sums give A063805. For nondegenerate matroids see A063851.
